l limit, they should harbour undermassive\nsecondaries and massive white dwarfs, near the Chandrasekhar limit, which would\nmake them excellent candidates for progenitors of supernovae type Ia.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 15 Jan 2004 01:11:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-11-11"}
